              <span slot="content">Monty Python&#39;s sharpest film, thanks to the actors delivering a mix of brilliant performances along with a smart story that makes fun of religiosity.  The troop remains brilliant, bouncing between different roles effortlessly, from a Roman Centurion to a mad prophet.  Graham Chapman is especially effective a Brian, a simple man who keeps getting confusing for a prophet when he&#39;s just trying to do the right thing.  Behind the camera, this is a sharp commentary on religion, not attacking Jesus but how followers misinterpret his words and beliefs.  Plus, it&#39;s mixed in with some absurdist humor, from speech impediments to alien attacks.  While not as funny as &quot;Holy Grail&quot;, definitely Monty Python&#39;s smartest film.</span>
